race.description: Ladbrokes 55 Second Challenge Series 2 Ht 5 Hcp (Bm66)
race.comment: Looks a great race for EGERTON (1), who was never a factor last start but was a good Flemington winner in BM66 the start prior. This too is a BM66 but there looked to be more depth at Flemington. The only knock is that he gets back, and it can sometimes be tough to make ground here, especially in sprint races. FULLY CALCULATED (5) has been finding it hard to break through of late, but by the same token is not running poorly. The gate is a potential disaster, but offsetting that is the 3kg claim for in-form apprentice Jackson Radley. SYMPHONY OF COLOUR (4) was given a good chance first-up for the new stable last time off the back of some good trials, but never looked likely. Might be worth another chance given the good confidence there. INNOCENT ENUFF (2) will go forward and is expected to be in the finish. This is the biggest test for SUPERVISE (3), but he's done little wrong in his career to date and could step up here.
